Salem Al Ketbi is an Emirati political analyst, researcher and opinion writer. 
Al Ketbi has a Ph.D. in Public Law and Political Science from the Hassan II University in Casablanca for his thesis entitled "Political and religious propaganda and leadership through the social media in the Arab World".[1] 
He has for newspapers and media outlets including Gulf News,[2] Al Arabiya,[3] the London-based Al-Arab,[4] Morocco's Al-Alam[5] and Hespress,[6] as well as some research centers.[7] Al Ketbi writes on UAE national security, Iranian foreign policy, terror organizations and extremist groups.[7] 
