Irene Aurelia Tarimo (born Kilimanjaro, published as T. A. Irene) is an environmental scientist, and the Head of Department of Environmental Studies at the Open University of Tanzania. 
She is also a lecturer and researcher at OUT.[1] She was a director of the Lindi Regional Centre of the Open University of Tanzania for almost nine years. 
Irene is very keen in her academic career . She is a professional teacher, she teaches undergraduate and postgraduate courses, conducts research and publishes academic articles. Her research interests include pollution control, environmental cleanliness, effects of toxic heavy metals, health ethics, waste management and natural wastewater treatment methods using constructed wetlands . 
Irene is a sports enthusiast, she's frequently follow world news and events. She is also involved in community activities like taking care of the environment and helping the needy.[citation needed] 
Irene received a prize during her National Service attachment, was awarded a Certificate of Recognition for Climbing Mount Kilimanjaro by the late Mwalimu Julius Nyerere.[citation needed] 
