Elsie A. B. Effah Kaufmann (born 7 September 1969[1][2]) is a Ghanaian academic, biomedical engineer and current Host of the National Science and Maths Quiz.[3][4][5] Before Elsie Kaufmann started hosting the show in 2006, Marian Ewurama Addy was the Quiz Mistress from 1993 to 2000 and Eureka Emefa Adomako from 2001 to 2005.[3][6] In December 2020, Elsie Kaufmann was appointed an associate professor at the University of Ghana.[7] 
The daughter of educators, she hails from Assin in the Central Region.[8] Kaufmann had her secondary education at the Aburi Girls' Senior High School. 
She obtained her International Baccalaureate Diploma from United World College of the Atlantic in Wales in 1988. 
She proceeded to the University of Pennsylvania for her Bachelor of Science in Engineering (BSE), a Master of Science in Engineering (MSE) and PhD in Bioengineering.[9] 
