He studied art at the Community Arts Project under Cecil Skotnes[4][5] between 1982 and 1987. 
He was active in the formation of the Mitchells Plain Art Group in 1988. 
He has held numerous local and international art exhibitions, and in 2008 released his first volume of poetry. 
