Johannes Phokela (born 1966[1]) is a South African painter and sculptor. 
References 
Background 
Johannes Phokela was born in Soweto, South Africa in 1966 and trained under Durant Sihlali.[2] 
When Phokela was a child he witnessed the Soweto uprising and later created memorials regarding the event,[3] including a statue of Teboho MacDonald Mashinini on the grounds of Morris Isaacson High School unveiled on 1 May 2010,[4] and a large sculptural mural of a book sitting in a lot opposite of the school.[3] 
Sarah Richards with wax model of her bronze sculpture of a school boy. 
Sarah Richards (born 28 September 1968) is a South African sculptor working in bronze. 
From 1985 to 1990 she studied fine art at the Durban Technikon, where she majored in sculpture. 
During the next four years she travelled overseas to gain experience and insight. 
She then returned to Durban to make and teach art. 
She completed her master's degree in fine art (cum laude) at the Durban University of Technology in 2008. 
Richards lives and practises art in the KwaZulu-Natal midlands of South Africa.[1] 
