Chris Chameleon (born 28 July 1971) is a South African musician. 
He is the lead singer and bass guitarist for the band Boo!,[1] and a solo artist. 
Chris has experience as an actor, making his debut in Franz Marx's Sonkring in the early 1990s, performing a role on 7de Laan as a musician, and starring in the South African soap opera, Binneland Sub Judice. 
Chris Chameleon was born Chris Mulder on Wednesday, 28 July 1971. 
Chameleon released his debut album, Ek Herhaal Jou, in 2005. 
It consists of the poems of Ingrid Jonker set to music. 
"Ek Herhaal Jou", and was nominated for a South African Music Award (SAMA) for Best Adult Contemporary Afrikaans Album in 2006. 
