Warda Al-Jazairia (Arabic: وردة الجزائرية; born Warda Ftouki (وردة فتوكي); 22 July 1939 – 17 May 2012) was an Algerian-Lebanese singer. She was well known for her Egyptian Arabic songs and music. Her name literally meant Warda the Algerian, but she was sometimes referred to as just Warda (Egyptian Arabic: [ˈwæɾdæ] meaning "Rose") or as "The Algerian Rose" in the Arab world. 
Early life 
Warda Ftouki was born in Paris on July 22, 1939. 
Her father, Mohammed Ftouki, was an Algerian from Souk Ahras, and her mother was Lebanese.[2] She was the youngest of five children.[3][4] 
