Dourouf El Guaddar (Arabic: ظروف الكدار; born 16 April 1979) known professionally as Nores, is a Moroccan rapper and music producer.[1] 
References 
Early life 
Nores was born on 16 April 1979 in Salé, Morocco.[2] 
Nores got into Hip Hop in the mid 1995. 
In 1997, he founded—along with other rappers from Salé— the rap group Siouf El Borj which had initial success locally until its members separated in 1999. In 2006, he produced—along with DBF, DJ VAN, and Thug Face—an album for Don Bigg titled Mgharba ‘Tal Moute. 
He produced for many other hip hop artists in Morocco including Fatiwizz, Majesticon, Loubna, Tar, Sator and Rabat Crew. 
In 2007, he released his first album "Bit Ennar" containing 17 songs.[3][4] 
