Marvellous Efe Odiete (born 6 September 1978) is a Nigerian gospel singer and songwriter.[1][2] 
Early life and education 
Odiete was born on 6 September 1978 in Sapele, Delta State into a Christian family. 
He was introduced to music in his early years[vague] through the influence of his father Bishop John Odiete.[1] He grew up in the church circles and started playing the bass guitar at age 12. 
He studied political science at the University of Ibadan.[1] 
He was first runner up in MTN Project Fame (Season 5).[3][4] After a long hiatus he released various singles such as "Blow you a kiss", "You are worthy" and "I am not Alone".[5][6][7] 
