Stella Nyambura Mwangi (born 1 September 1986)[1] is a Kenyan-Norwegian singer, rapper and songwriter.[2] Much of her music concerns the situation in her home country Kenya, and discrimination her family had to endure after moving to Norway in 1991.[3] Her work has been used in films such as American Pie Presents: The Naked Mile and Save the Last Dance 2, and also in TV-series such as CSI: NY and Scrubs.[4] In Norway, she won the Melodi Grand Prix 2011, and in that same year represented Norway at the Eurovision Song Contest 2011 in Düsseldorf, Germany. 
USuzanna (Suzzana) Owíyo is a Kenyan singer. 
In 2006, she traveled to the United States to visit the University of Florida to help start an Arts in Medicine program at Mater Hospital in Nairobi.[1] 
Owíyo was part of the Divas of The Nile supergroup, that featured four Kenyan female musicians. 
The others were Mercy Myra, Achieng Abura and Princess Jully. 
The group performed at the Festival Mundial in 2007.[2] 
In 2008, she performed at the Nelson Mandela's 90th birthday concert in London and performed again at the WOMEX festival.[4] 
