Sona Jobarteh (born 1983[1]) is a British multi-instrumentalist, singer and composer with Gambian roots. 
She is from one of the five principal kora-playing griot families of West Africa, and is the first female professional kora player[1][2] to come from a griot family. 
She is the cousin of the celebrated kora player Toumani Diabate, and is the sister of the diaspora kora player Tunde Jegede.[3] 
