Shweta Mohan (born 19 November 1985)[2] is an Indian playback singer. 
She has received four Filmfare Awards South for Best Female Playback Singer, one Kerala State Film Award and one Tamil Nadu State Film Award. 
She has recorded more than 700 songs for film music and albums in all the four south Indian languages namely Malayalam, Tamil, Telugu, Kannada in addition to the Hindi films and has established herself as a leading playback singer of South Indian cinema. 
Shweta Mohan was born on 19 November 1985 to a Malayali family in Chennai, Tamil Nadu. 
She is the daughter of Krishna Mohan and playback singer Sujatha Mohan. 
She completed schooling at Good Shepherd Convent, Chennai and graduated from Stella Maris College, Chennai.[3] She is married to her long-time friend, Ashwin Shashi.[4] Shweta Mohan and Ashwin Shashi have a daughter, Sresta Ashwin, who was born in 2017.[1] 
