Kyriakos Mitsotakis (Greek: Κυριάκος Μητσοτάκης, Kyriákos Mitsotákis [ciɾˈʝakos mit͡soˈtacis]; born 4 March 1968) is a Greek politician who has been serving as the prime minister of Greece since 2019. 
A member of New Democracy, he has been its president since 2016. 
He was previously Leader of the Opposition between 2016 and 2019, and Minister of Administrative Reform between 2013 and 2015. 
Mitsotakis was first elected to the Hellenic Parliament for the Athens B constituency in 2004. 
After New Democracy's two election defeats in 2015, he was elected the party's leader in January 2016. 
Three years later, he led his party to a majority in the 2019 election. 
